<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key Eb, 6/8. G#° non-diatonic → substituted with Cm (⑥m) throughout.
- LH "33" open triads alternating Eb-Cm-Bb. RH light thirds.
- Natural F (accid="n") treated as raised 2nd passing tone → B♭ dominant approach.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH holds Eb2-Bb2-Eb3 as pedal through most of the hymn.
- RH ascends to G5 at chorus bars 3 and 11.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Gentle 6/8 lilt; verses 1-2 consistent; chorus fuller at bars 9-12; climax bar 13 (Cm high); quiet Eb close.
-->
